      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GRANDINI (6) missed the start then made a long, sustained run to get up for third last start over 1400m at Tamworth. Perfectly placed out to this distance at the third run back. Might need luck at some stage from that inside draw as she gets back but if things go right she is the one to beat. ARE YOU KIDDING (1) is the X-factor after his demolition job in a 1500m Muswellbrook maiden last time out. That was on a heavy track so he has to bring that form to a firmer surface, but the dominance of the win is hard to ignore. DAMASCUS GATE (5) also scored over 1500m in the wet at Muswellbrook recently, leading for home then hanging on gamely. Definitely a better horse in heavy going but can also feature on top of the ground. ROSES IMMINENTE (3) has struggled in a couple of Class 3 Highways of late, but she can improve sharply back in this grade. BIG SHORT (4) rarely wins but has a 60% top-three strike-rate at the mile so must go in trifectas and first fours.",
